The body of a man has been found near a town’s war memorial in Surrey. A passer-by made the discovery in Gostrey Meadow, Farnham, just before 6am this morning. Detectives are currently treating the death as unexplained. The area has been closed off to the public, with a blue forensic tent erected over the body. ‘Officers are currently on scene at Gostrey Meadow in Farnham following the discovery of a man’s body earlier this morning,’ a Surrey Police spokesperson said. ‘The death is currently being treated as unexplained and enquiries are ongoing. Gostrey Meadow will be inaccessible to the public for some time.’ Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.